comments: Suggs (ORL) and Taylor (IND) each make clean contact with the ball prior to incidental body and arm contact occurring as they each attempt to gain control of the jump ball.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: The ball touches Taylor's (IND) forearm last before going out of bounds.
Carter Jr. (ORL) is turning slightly as he sets the pick on Craig (IND) and Carter Jr. does not deliver the contact as the defensive switch takes place.
Taylor (IND) brings his right hand out toward Wagner (ORL) and marginal contact occurs to Wagner's side as he changes direction at the end of the drive.

Anthony (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position alongside Holiday (IND) and any marginal contact that occurs is the result of Holiday extending his right leg backward when he mishandles the inbound.
LeVert (IND) delivers contact to Anthony's (ORL) front that affects his driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) engages and disengages with Taylor (IND) as Taylor moves to set the pick.
Carter Jr. (ORL) extends his left hand forward and marginal contact occurs with LeVert's (IND) side after his gather.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in a screening position in LeVert's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Taylor (IND) brings his left arm down and initiates contact with Wagner's (ORL) right arm during the driving shot attempt.
Holiday (IND) and Carter Jr. (ORL) engage and disengage with one another as the defensive switch takes place during the pick.
LeVert (IND) goes to, not through, Anthony's (ORL) front and marginal contact occurs as LeVert slows his momentum near the free throw line.
LeVert's (IND) right leg extends outward following the release and marginal contact occurs with Anthony's (ORL) left foot as Anthony contests the jump shot attempt.
Taylor (IND) engages and disengages with Carter Jr. (ORL) off-ball.
Holiday (IND) is moving somewhat laterally when marginal body contact occurs with Anthony (ORL) prior to Anthony's gather.
Taylor (IND) brings his left hand toward Anthony (ORL) and marginal contact occurs to Anthony's back as the rebound falls into the lane.
Carter Jr. (ORL) brushes LeVert's (IND) right side and marginal contact occurs as LeVert starts his upward shooting motion.
Suggs (ORL) and Holiday (IND) come together at the same spot in the lane and marginal side-to-side body contact occurs during rebounding.

Wagner (ORL) releases his left forearm away from LeVert's (IND) front and marginal contact occurs after LeVert's gather. Carter Jr. (ORL) then brings his right hand toward LeVert and marginal contact takes place with LeVert's right side.

Anthony (ORL) brings both arms up during rebounding and marginal contact occurs with Taylor's (IND) head as Anthony makes simultaneous contact with the ball. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Carter Jr.'s (ORL) right arm moves backward as he pursues the rebound and marginal contact occurs with LeVert's (IND) front and head/neck area. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Taylor (IND) commits a take foul on Anthony (ORL).
Holiday (IND) releases the inbound within five seconds.
Harris (ORL) and LeVert (IND) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Harris (ORL) commits a take foul on LeVert (IND).
Anthony (ORL) and Duarte (IND) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Duarte (IND) commits a take foul on Anthony (ORL).
Suggs (ORL) commits a take foul on LeVert (IND).
Craig (IND) and Harris (ORL) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
LeVert's (IND) second free throw attempt does not make contact with the rim. Possession is awarded to Orlando.
Craig (IND) commits a take foul on Harris (ORL).
